This paper deals with a problem related to clustering points in a high-dimensional space, which is a common topic in computer science. The problem is defined in terms of rectangles, which suggests that it may be related to computational geometry (cs.CG). However, the problem is specifically about online algorithms, which suggests that it may be related to data structures (cs.DS) or algorithms (cs.AL). The fact that the problem is one-dimensional suggests that it may be related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents a lower bound on the competitive ratio of any deterministic online algorithm, which suggests that it may be related to complexity theory (cs.CC) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Overall, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC, and cs.AI seem like the most likely sub-categories, in descending order of likelihood.
